The paper deals with the challenge of searching for persons of interest among billions of shared photos on social media websites. This involves processing and searching large collections of unconstrained face images, which is a problem in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). 

The paper also involves searching for images on a large scale, which could fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) or cs.MM (Multimedia). Additionally, the paper proposes a system that combines deep features and a commercial off-the-shelf matcher, which could be relevant to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) or cs.LG (Machine Learning).
